    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-10-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-10-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="523"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d523">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.20/10–952</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by <persName>William B. Connett,
                            Jr.</persName>, of the Office of Middle American Affairs</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian"
                            type="conversation-or-meeting-date" when="1952-10-09">October 9,
                            1952</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>Subject:</head>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_SHADA1">SHADA</gloss>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <list type="participants">
                    <item>Participants: Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_LJ1">Jacques
                            Leger</persName>, Haitian Embassy</item>
                    <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MEG1">Miller</persName>—<gloss target="#t_ARA1"
                            >ARA</gloss>
                    </item>
                    <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MTC1">Mann</persName>—<gloss target="#t_ARA1"
                            >ARA</gloss>
                    </item>
                    <item>Mr. <persName>Connett</persName>—<gloss target="#t_MID1">MID</gloss>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p>Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_LJ1">Leger</persName> spoke of an impasse which
                    has occurred between the Haitian negotiating committee on <gloss
                        target="#t_SHADA1">Shada</gloss>, headed up by Finance Minister <persName
                        corresp="#p_DA1">Dominique</persName>, and the Export-Import Bank.<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d523fn1">Between late September and early November 1952, a
                        mission representing the Haitian Government held a series of discussions
                        with representatives of the Export-Import Bank at Washington for the purpose
                        of resolving the <gloss target="#t_SHADA1">SHADA</gloss> problem.</note>
                    Specifically, he said the Bank had proposed reducing the interest rate from 4 to
                    2 percent, extending the period of repayment of the indebtedness, and
                    liquidating <gloss target="#t_SHADA1">Shada</gloss>. The Ambassador said this
                    proposal was unacceptable to the Haitian Mission which wished to have the debt
                    cancelled or substantially reduced. Consequently, Ambassador <persName
                        corresp="#p_LJ1">Leger</persName> said, the Mission was preparing to return
                    to Haiti within a week or so.</p>
                <p>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MEG1">Miller</persName> and Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_MTC1">Mann</persName> informed Ambassador <persName
                        corresp="#p_LJ1">Leger</persName> that the latter would pay Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_GHE1">Gaston</persName> a visit the following day to see if the
                    State Department’s good offices might have some effect in resolving the
                    impasse.</p>
            </div>
